node.text:
Life on the edge!
We hope that Jeff, Jeri, Atlas, and their fur babies NEVER need our products, but they have them “just in case” !

from @thisisironclad
•
Giving fear the middle finger.

In this episode, meet Jeff, a former Navy SEAL, and his wife, Jeri, a physician assistant, who move to Alaska to start a new life on their own homestead. 

Along with their team of sled dogs, Jeff and Jeri embark on a journey north of the Arctic Circle in pursuit of the Porcupine caribou herd to try and fill the freezer for the year.

New episodes every week.

@frozentrident 
@mrs_ftk

node.text: Whether negligence is involved, or just a freak accident, we all know anything can happen on the water. The question is, will you be prepared to save a life? Could be an accident on your boat, a situation 50 miles offshore, or a problem that you just so happened to be first on the scene. Will you be ready? It’s something as mariners we all don’t think about as much as we should, and I’m here to raise awareness so you as the captain will be ready to save a life. We teamed up with @northamericanrescue and @pelicanprofessional to help provide all captains with the best and most affordable Qualified Captain Trauma Kit. It is specifically dialed in with the medical equipment you will need for when things go south. I treat these kits like an EPIRB. I don’t leave with out one whether it’s my boat, a friends boat, or a commercial boat. More information about the kits are on our website. Go check them out today, and always be prepared. Thank you @djstruntz @northamericanrescue and @pelicanprofessional to help make this happen. At the end of the day, we all want to have a good time and make it home safe. Have a great week everyone. #qualified #qualifiedcaptaintraumakits #beprepared #savealife #northamericanrescue #pelicancase #collobration

node.text:
The best kind of #mondaymotivation 
from @effective.fitnesstraining
•
If this isn’t motivation to be a strong and prepared individual; I don’t know what is.

This is why it’s critical to prepare your body for high level performance. Multiple factors play into the physical development and growth of an individual: nutrition, programming, recovery, etc.

Remember, we can’t fail. Prepared to win. If you don’t know where to start we can help. LFG🏴

Backstory: 2 Officers in Yonkers, NY saved a baby stuck underneath a car. The incident occurred after an allegedly drunk driver drove into a building and hit the baby and her mother.

node.title: Hero officers lift car off of baby!

node.text:
Repost from @uscg_rs
•
#USCG Sector Humboldt Bay aircrew rescued 2 sailors and 2 dogs 30 miles south of Cape Mendocino on Wednesday.

The sailors were beset by 15-20 foot seas and 30kt winds and contacted Sector watchstanders in distress.

A MH-65D Aircrew deployed, hoisted the sailors and dogs from the water and transferred them to Mendocino Coast Hospital in stable condition. #BZ

🎥 @uscgpacarea

node.text:
“As I sit here with my team in Qatar, safe from the chaos, I’m trying to think of the right words to explain what we just saw in Kabul. We witnessed a humanitarian crisis that will likely turn into wholesale assassinations, murder, sex slavery, and human trafficking. On 15 August 2021, the city of Kabul fell to the Taliban.  In the days that followed, we pushed our physical and emotional limits to a near breaking point, and I couldn’t be more proud to be a part of the leadership team that took decisive action to defy the Taliban and rescue as many people as we could. During our last 16 days at HKIA, we were privileged to be the last Pararescue team in Afghanistan after 20 years of combat operations. We worked with highly professional joint and interagency teams, as well as COMTF, conducting hi-risk recovery operations and ultimately saving 1500-2000 lives. This group consists of AMCITs, Afghan soldiers and SOF operators, pilots, female soldiers, GIRoA government officials, high-risk civilians, and most importantly, children. The collective effort rescued thousands. As we speak, the Taliban is going door-to-door in Kabul, marking the homes of young single females (some children) so they can claim them as wives. These women and children will ultimately be kidnapped and raped under the veil of sharia law. A vast majority of these people had already received written death threats, been beaten, and had their homes taken from them by the Taliban. This historical event needs to be told. Leaving Afghanistan at this juncture feels wrong, especially after watching 13 of our brothers and sisters take their final flight on a C-17 in flag-draped coffins.”
#thatothersmaylive #bethedifference

While we have been focused on the lives lost, let us not forget those who survived the blast and those providing their care! To all those injured we extend our hopes for rapid and complete recoveries and to the echelons of caregivers ranging from medics to Techs, nurses, PAs, and Doctors THANK YOU for being there to care for our wounded!

from @militaryhealth
•
U.S. Soldiers, Airmen and civilian staff at Landstuhl Regional Medical Center receive casualties who were medically evacuated from Kabul, #Afghanistan, after U.S. service members and Afghan civilians were injured in a series of attacks outside of Hamid Karzai International Airport in #Kabul Aug. 26 and transported to LRMC for further care. #MilitaryHealth #AroundTheMHS #MilitaryMedicine #HKIA

node.text:
This morning our hearts are heavy as the catastrophic effects of Hurricane Ida are becoming known. Our thoughts and prayers are with both the victims and those responding to this terrible storm 🙏🏼💪🏼🇺🇸

from @weatherchannel
•
Rescue crews are still trying to reach residents who became trapped in their own homes by rising waters in several parts of southern Louisiana.

In some areas, people resorted to posting on social media that they needed to be rescued because 911 service was knocked out by widespread power outages that have left more than 1 million homes and businesses in the dark.

The situation remains dire across southeastern Louisiana, and we are tracking all the latest developments. Tap the link in our bio for continuing coverage, and stay tuned to The Weather Channel.

📸: Live Storms Media

#Ida #Louisiana #LAwx

node.text:
They believed in saving the lives of our friends and their families in Afghanistan. Let us actively honor their legacy by shepherding those they died defending. It isn’t about religion or politics, its about human decency and the American Dream.  Lady Liberty is more than a monument, she is all of our hopes and ideals embodied. We face storms of polarizing division, but we need to take a good hard look in the mirror and remember that we are AMERICANS and it is imperative that we act like it.  Those we lost did, and their final actions were helping those in dire need.  BE THE DIFFERENCE 🙏🏼🇺🇸🇦🇫

#honorthefallen 
#bethedifference 
#mondaymotivation

That sick to your stomach feeling that just won’t go away… for each precious one we lost, but now in this moment, we honor Max 🙏🏼🇺🇸💔

from @the_resuscitationist
This one hurts.

Max is one of our own. He was killed yesterday during the attack while serving as a Navy Corpsman "Doc". Many of us interacted with him on this platform. Thank you for your selflessness. It does not go unnoticed.

Rest easy Max, you are not forgotten.
